    <workgroup>Transport Layer Security</workgroup>
    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;This document specifies an optional behavior of Transport Layer Security (TLS) client implementations, dubbed "False Start".  It affects only protocol timing, not on-the-wire protocol data, and can be implemented unilaterally.  A TLS False Start reduces handshake latency to one round trip.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
